    {
      "type": "text",
      "body": "\n        Podzielimy razem wielomian \\(2x^3-9x^2+13x+1\\) przez \\(2x-3\\).\n    "
    },
    {
      "type": "spoiler",
      "label": "rozwiÄ…zanie",
      "body": "\n\n<div class=\"steps\">\n<p>\n                Zapiszmy dziaĹ‚anie pod kreskÄ… tak, jakbyĹ›my dzielili liczby:\n            </p>\n<div class=\"table_wrapper\">\n<table class=\"my_table_noborder table_centered\" data-cellwidth=\"40px\">\n<tr style=\"border-bottom: 1px solid black;\">\n<td>\n                            \\(\\)\n                        </td>\n<td>\n                            \\(\\)\n                        </td>\n<td>\n                            \\(\\)\n                        </td>\n<td>\n                            \\(\\)\n                        </td>\n<td>\n                            \\(\\)\n                        </td>\n<td>\n                            \\(\\)\n                        </td>\n<td>\n                            \\(\\)\n                        </td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n                            \\((2x^3\\)\n                        </td>\n<td>\n                            \\(-9x^2\\)\n                        </td>\n<td>\n                            \\(+13x\\)\n                        </td>\n<td>\n                            \\(+1)\\)\n                        </td>\n<td>\n                            \\(:\\)\n                        </td>\n<td>\n                            \\((2x\\)\n                        </td>\n<td>\n                            \\(-3)\\)\n                        </td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n</div>\n<p>\n                Tym razem nie rozpatrujemy kolejnych\n                <u>\n                    cyfr\n                </u>\n                liczby, lecz kolejne\n                <u>\n                    wyrazy\n                </u>\n                wielomianu, takĹĽe od lewej.\n            </p>\n<div class=\"show_next ks_button\">\n                pokaĹĽ dalej\n            </div>\n<div class=\"show_step\">\n<p>\n                    Dodatkowo, dla uĹ‚atwienia, nie bÄ™dziemy dzialiÄ‡ przez caĹ‚y dzielnik \\((2x-3)\\), lecz tylko przez jego poczÄ…tkowy wyraz, \\(2x\\).\n                </p>\n<p>\n                    Najpierw\n                    <strong>\n                        dzielimy\n                    </strong>\n                    \\(2x^3\\) przez \\(2x\\):\n                </p>\n                \\[\n                                               \\frac{2x^3}{2x}=x^2\n                                               \\]\n                <div class=\"table_wrapper\">\n<table class=\"my_table_noborder table_centered\" data-cellwidth=\"40px\">\n<tr style=\"border-bottom: 1px solid black;\">\n<td class=\"red_on_yellow\">\n                                \\(x^2\\)\n                            </td>\n<td>\n                                \\(\\)\n                            </td>\n<td>\n                                \\(\\)\n                            </td>\n<td>\n                                \\(\\)\n                            </td>\n<td>\n                                \\(\\)\n                            </td>\n<td>\n                                \\(\\)\n                            </td>\n<td>\n                                \\(\\)\n                            </td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"red_on_yellow\">\n                                \\((2x^3\\)\n                            </td>\n<td>\n                                \\(-9x^2\\)\n                            </td>\n<td>\n                                \\(+13x\\)\n                            </td>\n<td>\n                                \\(+1)\\)\n                            </td>\n<td>\n                                \\(:\\)\n                            </td>\n<td class=\"red_on_yellow\">\n                                \\((2x\\)\n                            </td>\n<td>\n                                \\(-3)\\)\n                            </td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"show_next ks_button\">\n                pokaĹĽ dalej\n            </div>\n<div class=\"show_step\">\n<p>\n                    Teraz\n                    <strong>\n                        mnoĹĽymy\n                    </strong>\n                    wynik \\(x^2\\) przez\n                    <u>\n                        caĹ‚y dzielnik\n                    </u>\n                    \\((2x-3)\\) i zapisujemy rezultat poniĹĽej:\n                </p>\n<div class=\"table_wrapper\">\n<table class=\"my_table_noborder table_centered\" data-cellwidth=\"40px\">\n<tr style=\"border-bottom: 1px solid black;\">\n<td class=\"red_on_yellow\">\n                                \\(x^2\\)\n                            </td>\n<td>\n                                \\(\\)\n                            </td>\n<td>\n                                \\(\\)\n                            </td>\n<td>\n                                \\(\\)\n                            </td>\n<td>\n                                \\(\\)\n                            </td>\n<td>\n                                \\(\\)\n                            </td>\n<td>\n                                \\(\\)\n                            </td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n                                \\((2x^3\\)\n                            </td>\n<td>\n                                \\(-9x^2\\)\n                            </td>\n<td>\n                                \\(+13x\\)\n                            </td>\n<td>\n                                \\(+1)\\)\n                            </td>\n<td>\n                                \\(:\\)\n                            </td>\n<td class=\"red_on_yellow\">\n                                \\((2x\\)\n                            </td>\n<td class=\"red_on_yellow\">\n                                \\(-3)\\)\n                            </td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"red_on_yellow\">\n                                \\(2x^3\\)\n                            </td>\n<td class=\"red_on_yellow\">\n                                \\(-3x^2\\)\n                            </td>\n<td>\n                                \\(\\)\n                            </td>\n<td>\n                                \\(\\)\n                            </td>\n<td>\n                                \\(\\)\n                            </td>\n<td>\n                                \\(\\)\n                            </td>\n<td>\n                                \\(\\)\n                            </td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"show_next ks_button\">\n                pokaĹĽ dalej\n            </div>\n<div class=\"show_step\">\n<p>\n<strong>\n                        Odejmujemy\n                    </strong>\n                    i spisujemy kolejne wyrazy.\n                </p>\n<p>\n<strong>\n                        Uwaga\n                    </strong>\n                    !\n                </p>\n                Odejmujemy \\((2x^3-9x^2)-(2x^3-3x^2)\\)\n                <ul>\n<li>\n                        \\(2x^3-2x^3\\) to oczywiĹ›cie \\(0\\) (zwyczajowo zapisujemy dwie kreski \"\\(=\\)\").\n                    </li>\n<li>\n                        Drugie odejmowanie to \\(-9x^2-(-3x^2)\\). ZwrĂłÄ‡ uwagÄ™, ĹĽe odejmujemy \\(-3x^2\\), wiÄ™c wynikiem bÄ™dzie \\(-9x^2+3x^2=-6x^2\\).\n                    </li>\n</ul>\n                MoĹĽemy caĹ‚oĹ›Ä‡ zapisaÄ‡:\n                                               \\[\n                                               (2x^3-9x^2)-(2x^3-3x^2)=2x^3-9x^2-2x^3+3x^2=-6x^2\n                                               \\]\n                <div class=\"table_wrapper\">\n<table class=\"my_table_noborder table_centered\" data-cellwidth=\"40px\">\n<tr style=\"border-bottom: 1px solid black;\">\n<td>\n                                \\(x^2\\)\n                            </td>\n<td>\n                                \\(\\)\n                            </td>\n<td>\n                                \\(\\)\n                            </td>\n<td>\n                                \\(\\)\n                            </td>\n<td>\n                                \\(\\)\n                            </td>\n<td>\n                                \\(\\)\n   